<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1998295 lazyload lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Positive-and-negative-impact-of-love.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="852" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Positive-and-negative-impact-of-love.jpg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Positive-and-negative-impact-of-love-320x213.jpg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Positive-and-negative-impact-of-love-600x399.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Being in love and physical affection can have several positive effects on both physical and mental health. First some signs of being in love include: Now the positive impact of being in love include: Reduces stress: Love and physical affection release oxytocin, a hormone that can help reduce stress levels and improve overall well-being. Increases happiness: The feelings of happiness and contentment associated with being in love can have a positive impact on mental health. Boosts immunity: Oxytocin is also linked to a stronger immune system, helping to fight off illness and disease. Improves cardiovascular health: Physical affection can also increase heart rate and blood flow, promoting cardiovascular health. Enhances self-esteem: Feeling loved and valued in a relationship can boost self-esteem and confidence. What are the indicators of being in love? Overall, love and physical affection play important roles in promoting both physical and mental health, and can contribute to a happier, healthier life. It is important to note that everyone experiences love differently and these benefits may vary for each individual. 